33. Differential Privacy Trade-Off

Increasing noise multiplier improves privacy:

Lower ε
Stronger privacy

However:

Accuracy decreases
Utility degrades

This creates the privacy–utility trade-off central to DP learning.

Scientific Interpretation

The implementation demonstrates that:

Evolutionary optimization effectively discovers high-performing LSTM architectures with high privacy and low privacy budget.
DP-SGD introduces controlled utility degradation while protecting sensitive IoT traffic patterns.
Hyperparameter tuning substantially affects both privacy and utility.
Noise multiplier and clipping norm are dominant privacy-sensitive parameters.
